This paper deals with modeling and analyzing the performance of wireless networks with heterogeneous traffic and interference, which is a common problem in the field of networked systems and communication. The paper specifically focuses on the Internet-of-things (IoT) and its impact on wireless connectivity in unlicensed bands. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis of the performance of wireless networks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the impact of multipath fading on the performance of an interfered link, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with the issue of interference, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
